                  <msItem class="#funerary.epitaph">
                     <p>epitaph of Marcus Publilius Lupercus, doctor and surgeon</p>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc ana="#slab">
                     <supportDesc ana="#stone.marble">
                        <support>
                           <p>
                              <seg type="material">marble</seg>
                              <seg type="form">broken columbarium slab</seg>
                           </p>
                              <dimensions type="surface" unit="cm">
                                 <width>26.7</width>
                                 <height>11.7</height>
                              </dimensions>
                        </support>
                        <condition ana="fragments.contig">
                           <p>Broken into 4 or perhaps 5 pieces, reassembled with light grey putty and set into plaster with a wooden frame. The top half of the left ansa is broken off from spud hole up; a small triangle has broken off from right ansa, where an iron nail was driven. Traces of rust around each hole. The breakages make the strokes at the end of line 3 difficult to read.</p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" writtenLines="4">
                           <p>The even lines are indented to the right approximately one letter. <!-- Text bordered by incised triangles that act as borders on left and right sides. No obvious indications of guidelines --></p>
                        </layout>
                        <layout>
                           <dimensions type="campus" unit="cm">
                              <height unit="cm">12.1</height>
                              <width unit="cm">18.7</width> <!-- Added dimensions of text area-->
                        </dimensions></layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc ana="#impressed.inscribed.chiseled">
                     <handNote>Fine shading, small serifs. The letter G curls back . Loop of P does not close fully and is small. Upper loop of letter B is the same size as this, with a larger lower loop. A small tail curves up and to the right at the end of the letter R and this is even more pronounced on the final A of barba.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote ana="tabula.ansata">
                        <p>Right-angled corners sunken into corners to create tabula ansata motif.</p>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
               </physDesc>
